title: Biological Evolution S210
prompt: If light-toned crickets and dark-toned crickets had evolved so significantly that they could no longer interbreed, this would be an example of
feedback: Two different living populations of the same species may undergo different evolutionary changes due to natural selection. Those two populations may diverge significantly and become separate species. This process is called speciation. A species can only interbreed with an organism of the same species. If the two colorations of cricket could not longer interbreed, this would indicate that they had diverged into two distinct species.
